description.narrative: The USAID Quality Health Care Project is a five-year program to improve the health status of Central Asians by incorporating modern quality improvement techniques and evidence-based international standards into ongoing reforms of health systems to assist Central Asian countries to improve their management, financing, and implementation of health services related to tuberculosis, HIV/AIDS, maternal and child health services and cardiovascular disease.
